headline: GE Aerospace Collaboration on Advanced SiC Devices Could Be a Game Changer for Axcelis Technologies (ACLS)
summary: GE Aerospace recently announced a joint development program with Axcelis Technologies to advance production-worthy high-voltage silicon carbide superjunction power devices using the Purion XEmax™ high energy implanter. This collaboration highlights the important role of silicon carbide semiconductors for enabling innovation in aerospace, defense, artificial intelligence, and other emerging high-growth sectors.
